Jordi recently completed an MSc in Neuroscience at UCL, after earning a BSc in Biotechnology from the University of Barcelona in Spain. He is using a 2D virtual reality platform to investigate the neural signatures of path integration in rodents, in collaboration with Neil Burgess.
